  "prompt": "How can NRI apply in Form 13 for lower TDS deduction?",
  "response": "Here's a step-by-step guide for NRIs applying for Form 13 to get lower TDS deduction:\n\n1. Purpose of Form 13\n- Request lower TDS rate from income sources in India\n- Used by NRIs to claim reduced tax deduction\n\n2. Eligibility\n- NRIs earning income in India\n- Income subject to TDS\n- Expecting lower tax liability\n\n3. Documents Required\n- PAN Card\n- Passport/Visa copy\n- NRI bank account details\n- Income proof\n- Tax residency certificate\n- Self-declaration of estimated total income\n\n4. Submission Process\n- Apply to Income Tax Assessing Officer\n- Submit Form 13 with supporting documents\n- Can be filed online or physically\n\n5. Key Information in Form 13\n- Personal details\n- Income source details\n- Estimated total income\n- Requested lower TDS rate\n\n6. Submission Timelines\n- Before start of financial year\n- At least 15 days before first TDS deduction\n\n7. Processing\n- Income Tax Department reviews application\n- Grants lower/nil TDS certificate if approved\n\n8. Validity\n- Certificate valid for specific financial year\n\nConsult a tax professional for personalized guidance.",
